&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;When you join our team, you’ll work alongside some of the most experienced leaders in the industry — professionals who share their knowledge freely and lead by example. You’ll be challenged, supported, and trusted to take ownership of meaningful work that shapes the future of one of the fastest-growing industries in America.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Field Operations Technician is a hands-on, highly mobile role that keeps our client retail locations running. You will be the person who shows up, figures it out, and gets it done — whether that means mounting security cameras, assembling fixtures, pulling cable, patching drywall, setting up a new POS terminal, or driving three hours to our next location with a van full of equipment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is approximately 60% handyman, IT, and general installation work, 40% driving and field travel. You will work directly alongside our two IT Field Technicians and report to the Director of Corporate Operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are resourceful, physically capable, comfortable with tools and tech, and enjoy variety in your work — this role is for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU WILL DO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technology &amp;amp; Construction Support (Supporting Role)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist IT Field Technicians with installation of cameras, access control, alarm systems, networking equipment, and POS hardware&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run ethernet, connect network hardware, and verify basic connectivity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot basic technology issues at retail locations; escalate complex issues to the IT team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn new systems and techniques through hands-on experience and self-directed research&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform installations across retail locations: wall mounts, shelving, cabinetry, drawers, furniture, and fixtures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete basic drywall patching, painting, and light exterior work including signage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support store setups, refreshes, and remodel projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pull and route low-voltage cabling for technology and security systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work in a range of physical conditions including tight spaces, overhead environments, and confined areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify facility issues and escalate repairs as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Driving &amp;amp; Field Travel&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate a company-provided van to transport equipment and materials statewide&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel primarily to Twin Cities metro and southern Minnesota retail locations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete drives of 8+ hours as needed; occasional overnight stays required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use personal vehicle when needed; mileage reimbursement provided&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
